gn=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All these new MMORPG's, what do you think?</span><hr size=1> Ainwein will be making a return... In Star Wars Galaxies! <p>'Nuff said<br><br><br><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~slbush/wein.gif" ALIGN="left" ALT="[60 Virtuoso] Ainwein (Wood Elf) <Fellowship of the Blue-Eyed Monkey>"><br><b>Virtuoso</b><br><i>Ayonae Ro</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shewdogg>Shewdogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 10:26:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All these new MMORPG's, what do you think?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Ainwein will be making a return... In Star Wars Galaxies! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br><br>First you make a Eru Pally, now you're going to SWG? you're going on my shitlist, right under Shortyrez's spot <p><br</br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145719"> Shewdogg Mindbullets </a href><p> Rock Star Crusader of Final Destiny</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujamisiashido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jamisia Shido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 10:41:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All these new MMORPG's, what do you think?</span><hr size=1> Whatever happened to that fantasy MMORPG called Hero's Journey? Not that I ever thought much of it, but I just sort of noticed it completely fell off the edge of the proverbial digital world.<br><br>Middle Earth was cancelled too, from what I recall.<br><br>I had my fill of PVP on the Zeks; I was so disgusted at the spiral of newness to rubbish in such a *very* short period of time that I'll skip Shadowbane thankyouverymuch.<br><br>WoW is so far off I don't know what to think. It took Blizzard 5-6 years to make a Diablo II. Besides, while it visually appears well rendered (despite the fact the engine isn't done), it looks too much like a miniature Warhammer 40k game. That stuff never interested me.<br><br>Star Wars: Galaxies. This is a tough one. Star Wars feels tired, in terms of trying to open up the milieu to open-ended playing. But the game world and NPCs look great. I only question the *point* of the game. I swear, if I have to kill swamp rats, level for no purpose, etcetera, forget it. I can do that in EQ.<br><br>Neverwinter Nights interests me. A lot. So does tabletop roleplaying, but I don't do much of that anymore either. Not because I dislike it, just because schedules are so hard to mesh, etc. You get that sort of problem a lot with smaller games. I *love* small games, but timing is crucial. It'll definitely earn a place on my shelf, I only wonder how often I'll get the chance to play it with friends.<br><br>AC2 doesn't interest me. EQ2 is something I have to say 'wait and see' to. There was a lot of promise for EQ and it ended up a lot different than how I always envisioned it during early stages of beta. Too ... mechanical. The paths especially. Just yuck. Also the &quot;GM run quests!&quot; turned out to be a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   bug hunt</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. (Pretty obvious quote.) Very lackluster. Despite this I still play it. But it could've been so much better. I just don't want to see EQ2 turn out to be exactly like EQ but with slightly enhanced graphics.<br><br>Generally speaking, I want to move <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  up</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the ladder if I buy a new online game -- especially if it follows the monthly service feel model. It has to have something new, something compelled, something unique to the genre. (NWN, for instance, allows for direct DM control in a 64-person role-playing game. &lt;-- using this as an example, despite the fact it has no service fee involved it illustrates my point very well.) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujamisiashido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jamisia Shido</A> at: 6/21/02 7:12:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uicklymuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Icklymuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/21/02 5:24:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All these new MMORPG's, what do you think?</span><hr size=1> Oh, I forgot about the MAtrix MORP...<br><br>Ok for the life of me I don't get this, maybe its someones sick joke. But why make a Vast Online game about exscaping from a Vast online game? Do you get Phat loot just for logging out?<br><br>/boggle<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2616.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2616.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2616.topic&index=14><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table wid